<br>
I generally will not accept any payment unless there are special circumstances:<br>
<br>
1) I'm broke and need to buy peridots<br>
2) The rez request was in a really far off or hazardous zone.<br>
3) If I am required to leave the vicinity of my group do rez.  <br>
<br>
<br>
The offer of money is not to compensate me for mana expended, especially if I have an epic.  Mana is free right?  What is not free is my time.  We pay for our time online.  What is your time online worth?  <br>
In most cases if you are polite with your request and are understanding if I cant do it right at that minute, you'll not see me accept any payment.  This does not mean you should not offer it.  It is always polite to offer money, gems, loot, whatever for the cleric to take time out of his/her day to assist you with the regain of exp (i.e. your time lost) due to your own mistake.  We clerics are going to keep a mental log in the back of our heads as to who offers what and how much.  It's not greed, you know we in most cases won't accept it.  What you are again doing is being polite.  Saying hey, please let me offer you some money for your time I have taken out of your day.  This is especially true if we know you are in a zone that makes alot of money.  Druids, you know what I'm talking about here.  You are quad kiting in CS zone, you stand to make a decent living.  Well, dont offer like just 30pp, its insulting.  One hundred pp or around that area is a good gesture, not like you cannot make that up there, and odds are we're really not going to accept it anyway unless there's a special circumstance.  Afterall, you know when we're asking you for a port, you'd like some decent compensation.  Late nights, times you might be doing your own thing, the offer of 75-100pp for a lift helps make the time you took out of your day worth while. <br>
<br>
Hope this all makes some sense. <p></p><i></i></td></tr></table> </td></tr></table> <table border=0 width=95%><tr><td align=left valign="top">  Page <a href=http://pub41.ezboard.com/fthecrossroadstavern8833frm26.showMessageRange?topicID=11.topic&start=1&stop=20>1</a><a href=http://pub41.ezboard.com/fthecrossroadstavern8833frm26.showMessageRange?topicID=11.topic&start=21&stop=40>2</a> <b>3</b>  </td><td align=right valign="top"><a href="http://pub41.ezboard.com/fthecrossroadstavern8833frm26.showPrevMessage?topicID=11.topic"> << Prev Topic</a>&nbsp;| <a href="http://pub41.ezboard.com/fthecrossroadstavern8833frm26.showNextMessage?topicID=11.topic"> Next Topic >> </a><br><br><a href=http://pub41.ezboard.com/fthecrossroadstavern8833frm26.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=11.topic&index=41><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/themes/egyptian/addReply.gif border=0 alt="Add Reply"></a> </td></tr></table><br><table width=95% border=0><td valign="top"> <a href=http://pub41.ezboard.com/fthecrossroadstavern8833frm26.emailToFriend?topicID=11.topic><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/image/email.gif border=0 alt="Email This To a Friend"> Email This To a Friend</a><br> <a href=http://pub41.ezboard.com/fthecrossroadstavern8833frm26.threadControl?topicID=11.topic><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/themes/egyptian/deleteThread.gif border=0 alt="Topic Control Image"> Topic Commands (Moderator only)</a><br> <a href=http://pub41.ezboard.com/fthecrossroadstavern8833frm26.subscribeUnregisteredToTopic?topicID=11.topic>Subscribe</a> Click to receive email notification of replies<br>  <a href=http://pub41.ezboard.com/fthecrossroadstavern8833frm26.unsubscribeUnregisteredToTopic?topicID=11.topic>Unsubscribe</a> Click to stop receiving email notification of replies<br> </td><td align="right" valign="top"></td></tr><tr align="right"><td colspan=2><form action=http://pub41.ezboard.com/BBSForum.jumpShowForum method=post><table border="0" cellspacing="0" cellpa